author: News Release
title: Car-Pedestrian Traffic Accident in CJ
text:
CARL JUNCTION, MISSOURI - An 11-year-old Carl Junction boy is in serious condition after being hit by a 17-year-old driver while walking along Pennell and Grimes in Carl Junction Monday morning. Police Chief Delmar Hasse tells the incident is still under investigation, but police believe the boy entered onto the right of way on Pennell at Temple Street and was hit by an eastbound vehicle. Police are not yet releasing the names of those involved.
We will bring you more information as details are released.
